<article id=3D"content" role=3D"main">

<!-- #BeginEditable "Body" -->=20


<h1 class=3D"center">Interior Angles of Polygons</h1>=20


<p class=3D"large">An Interior Angle is an angle inside a shape:</p>=20
<p class=3D"center"><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/images/=
interior-exterior-angles.svg" alt=3D"interior exterior angles" height=3D"12=
5" width=3D"315"></p>=20
<p class=3D"large">Another example:</p>=20
<p class=3D"center"><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/images/=
interior-exterior-angles2.svg" alt=3D"interior exterior angles" height=3D"1=
82" width=3D"310"></p>=20


<h2>Triangles</h2>=20

<p class=3D"def large center">The Interior Angles of a Triangle add up to 1=
80=C2=B0</p><br>

<div class=3D"center">=20
<div class=3D"box"> Let's try a triangle:<br>
<img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/images/interior-angles-tria=
ngle1.svg" alt=3D"interior angles triangle 90 60 30" height=3D"140" width=
=3D"244"><span class=3D"larger"><br>
90=C2=B0 + 60=C2=B0 + 30=C2=B0 <em>=3D</em> 180=C2=B0</span>=20
<p>It works for this triangle</p>=20
</div>

<div class=3D"box"> Now tilt a line by 10=C2=B0:<br>
<img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/images/interior-angles-tria=
ngle2.svg" alt=3D"interior angles triangle 80 70 30" height=3D"140" width=
=3D"244"><br>
<span class=3D"larger"> 80=C2=B0 + 70=C2=B0 + 30=C2=B0 <em>=3D</em> 180=C2=
=B0</span>=20
<p>It still works!<br>
One angle went <b>up</b> by 10=C2=B0,<br>
and the other went <b>down</b> by 10=C2=B0</p>=20
</div>

</div>=20


<h2>Quadrilaterals (Squares, and so on)</h2>=20

<p>(A Quadrilateral has 4 straight sides)</p>=20
<div class=3D"centerfull">=20
<div class=3D"box">=20
<p>Let's try a square:<br>
<img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/images/interior-angles-squa=
re.svg" alt=3D"interior angles square 90 90 90 90" height=3D"140" width=3D"=
140"><span class=3D"larger"><br>
90=C2=B0 + 90=C2=B0 + 90=C2=B0 + 90=C2=B0 <em>=3D</em> 360=C2=B0</span></p>=
=20
<p>A Square adds up to 360=C2=B0</p>=20
</div>

<div class=3D"box">=20
<p>Now tilt a line by 10=C2=B0:<br>
<img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/images/interior-angles-quad=
.svg" alt=3D"interior angles 100 90 90 80" height=3D"140" width=3D"140"><sp=
an class=3D"larger"><br>
80=C2=B0 + 100=C2=B0 + 90=C2=B0 + 90=C2=B0 <em>=3D</em> 360=C2=B0</span></p=
>=20
<p>It still adds up to 360=C2=B0</p>=20
</div>

</div>=20

<p class=3D"def large center">The Interior Angles of a Quadrilateral add up=
 to 360=C2=B0</p>=20

<h3>Because there are 2 triangles in a square ...</h3>=20

<p class=3D"center"><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/images/=
interior-angles-square3.gif" alt=3D"interior angles 90 (45,45) 90 (45,45)" =
height=3D"163" width=3D"341"></p>=20
<p>The interior angles in a triangle add up to <b>180=C2=B0</b> ...</p>=20
<p class=3D"center">... and for the square they add up to <b>360=C2=B0</b> =
...</p>=20
<p class=3D"floatRt">... because the square can be made from two triangles!=
</p>=20
<div style=3D"clear:both"></div>


<h2>Pentagon</h2>=20

<p class=3D"floatLt"><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/images=
/interior-angles-pentagon.gif" alt=3D"interior angles pentagon" height=3D"1=
92" width=3D"201"></p>=20
<p>A pentagon has 5 sides, and can be made from <b>three triangles</b>, so =
you know what ...</p>=20
<p class=3D"center">... its interior angles add up to 3 =C3=97 180=C2=B0 <e=
m>=3D</em><b> 540=C2=B0</b></p>=20
<p>When the pentagon is <b>regular</b> (all angles equal), each angle is 54=
0<b>=C2=B0</b> / 5 <em>=3D</em> 108<b>=C2=B0</b></p>=20
<p><i>(Exercise: make sure each triangle here adds up to 180=C2=B0, and che=
ck that the pentagon's interior angles add up to 540=C2=B0)</i></p>=20
<p class=3D"def large center">The Interior Angles of a Pentagon add up to 5=
40=C2=B0</p>=20


<h2>The General Rule</h2>=20

<p>Each time we add a side (triangle to quadrilateral, then to pentagon, an=
d so on), we <b>add another 180=C2=B0</b> to the total:</p>=20
<div class=3D"simple">

	<table class=3D"center">
		<tbody><tr>
			<td class=3D"bg">&nbsp;</td>
			<td class=3D"bg">&nbsp;</td>
			<td class=3D"bg">&nbsp;</td>
			<td colspan=3D"2" class=3D"center">If it is a <b><a href=3D"https://www.=
mathsisfun.com/geometry/regular-polygons.html">Regular Polygon</a></b> (all=
 sides are equal, all angles are equal)</td>
		</tr>
		<tr class=3D"center">
			<th scope=3D"col">Shape</th>
			<th scope=3D"col">Sides</th>
			<th scope=3D"col">Sum of<br>
Interior Angles</th>
			<th scope=3D"col">Shape</th>
			<th scope=3D"col">Each Angle</th>
		</tr>
		<tr class=3D"center">
			<td><a href=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/triangle.html">Triangle</a></t=
d>
			<td>3</td>
			<td>180<b>=C2=B0</b></td>
			<td><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/images/triangle-regu=
lar.svg" alt=3D"regular triangle" height=3D"100" width=3D"110"></td>
			<td>60<b>=C2=B0</b></td>
		</tr>
		<tr class=3D"center">
			<td><a href=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/quadrilaterals.html">Quadrilat=
eral</a></td>
			<td>4</td>
			<td>360<b>=C2=B0</b></td>
			<td><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/images/quadrilateral=
-regular.svg" alt=3D"regular quadrilateral" height=3D"100" width=3D"110"></=
td>
			<td>90<b>=C2=B0</b></td>
		</tr>
		<tr class=3D"center">
			<td><a href=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/pentagon.html">Pentag=
on</a></td>
			<td>5</td>
			<td>540<b>=C2=B0</b></td>
			<td><b><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/images/pentagon-r=
egular.svg" alt=3D"pentagon regular" height=3D"100" width=3D"110"></b></td>
			<td>108<b>=C2=B0</b></td>
		</tr>
		<tr class=3D"center">
			<td><a href=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/hexagon.html">Hexagon=
</a></td>
			<td>6</td>
			<td>720<b>=C2=B0</b></td>
			<td><b><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/images/hexagon-re=
gular.svg" alt=3D"hexagon regular" height=3D"100" width=3D"110"></b></td>
			<td>120<b>=C2=B0</b></td>
		</tr>
		<tr class=3D"center">
			<td>Heptagon<br>
<i>(also called Septagon)</i></td>
			<td>7</td>
			<td>900<b>=C2=B0</b></td>
			<td><b><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/images/heptagon-r=
egular.svg" alt=3D"heptagon refular" height=3D"100" width=3D"110"></b></td>
			<td>128,57...<b>=C2=B0</b></td>
		</tr>
		<tr class=3D"center">
			<td>Octagon</td>
			<td>8</td>
			<td>1080<b>=C2=B0</b></td>
			<td><b><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/images/octagon-re=
gular.svg" alt=3D"octagon regular" height=3D"100" width=3D"110"></b></td>
			<td>135<b>=C2=B0</b></td>
		</tr>
		<tr class=3D"center">
			<td>Nonagon</td>
			<td>9</td>
			<td>1260<b>=C2=B0</b></td>
			<td><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/images/nonagon-regul=
ar.svg" alt=3D"nonagon regular" height=3D"100" width=3D"110"></td>
			<td>140<b>=C2=B0</b></td>
		</tr>
		<tr class=3D"center">
			<td>...</td>
			<td>...</td>
			<td>..</td>
			<td>...</td>
			<td>...</td>
		</tr>
		<tr class=3D"center">
			<td class=3D"larger">Any Polygon</td>
			<td><b class=3D"larger">n</b></td>
			<td class=3D"larger">(<b>n</b>=E2=88=922) =C3=97 180<b>=C2=B0</b></td>
			<td><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/images/n-gon-regular=
.svg" alt=3D"regular n gon" height=3D"100" width=3D"110"></td>
			<td class=3D"larger">(<b>n</b>=E2=88=922) =C3=97 180<b>=C2=B0</b> / <b>n=
</b></td>
		</tr>
	</tbody></table>=20
</div>=20

<p>So the general rule is:</p>=20
<div class=3D"def">=20
<p class=3D"larger">Sum of Interior Angles <em>=3D</em> (<b>n</b>=E2=88=922=
) =C3=97 180<b>=C2=B0</b></p>=20
<p class=3D"larger">Each Angle (of a Regular Polygon) <em>=3D</em> (<b>n</b=
>=E2=88=922) =C3=97 180<b>=C2=B0</b> / <b>n</b></p>=20
</div>=20

<p>Here's an example to make it clearer:</p>=20

<div class=3D"example">=20
	<h3>Example: What about a Regular Decagon (10 sides) ?</h3>=20

	<div class=3D"floatRt"><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/ima=
ges/decagon-regular.svg" alt=3D"regular decagon" height=3D"100" width=3D"11=
0"></div>

<div class=3D"two">=20
<div class=3D"lt">Sum of Interior Angles</div>

<div class=3D"rt">=3D (<b>n</b>=E2=88=922) =C3=97 180<b>=C2=B0</b></div>

<div class=3D"lt"></div>

